snippet.textDisplay:
I was actually rewarding the laser tag video, Then a thought came to my mind, what would happen if he came to lasertopia here in Canada? sure it might play out the same in a team battle, but power ups could change the tide of a battle easily, plus there’s different game modes like gladiator, free for all, zombies,

In gladiator everybody goes into a free for all, but with a twist! every time you get a certain amount of points, you go up a.rank, the leading player wins, while it’s pretty much like free for all, there’s one minor difference that makes a huge one, the higher the rank of the player you tag, the more points you get for doing so,

then there’s also zombies, which is pretty much... if you get tagged by a zombie you switch to their team, when a zombie gets tagged out they have to go back to a zombie spawn point (they appear in the places where power ups appear

Another gamemode I can’t remember the name of, was where there was one person who started out with a status effect, holding it would slowly earn them points, but once they got shot, whoever shot them takes that effect from them, also, you cannot tag somebody if they aren’t the one with the effect,

There’s also a unique feature of the battlefield, (it’s two floored but that’s not what I’m talking about)
laser gates. When a laser gate is red; Do. Not. Walk. Through. If you pass through a red laser gate, your weapon is disabled, (getting tagged out also has this effect, your weapon will re-enable after a short while) when a laser gate is white, it does nothing, if a laser gate is green, anybody who has a disabled weapon can walk through it to instantly enable their weapon, these gates are only located under where the second floor is

and about the aforementioned powerups, I should probably say what those are as well, the only two that I’ve seen (there’s probably more)
Is rapid fire, and double shield (powerups do not stack, and wear off after some time without warning ) rapid fire halves the delay between firing, recommended to use blaster (short ranged shotgun) double shield allows you to take two hits before going out, recommended to find a place with lots of coverage and use phaser (long ranged single shot) I can not stress how much you should avoid rushing in to a ton of enemies with double shield, it’s a one time use and will not protect you from laser gates, plus blaster tears through it with its multiple lasers

also if you get bored while waiting outside, you can play games in the arcade, or do a mission impossible based laser avoiding game
